<subSubSection box="[199,1126,836,861]" pageId="11" pageNumber="340" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,799,1256]" box="[199,1126,836,861]" pageId="11" pageNumber="340">
Type species. 
<taxonomicName authority="Nordmann, 1835" authorityName="Nordmann" authorityYear="1835" box="[356,768,836,861]" class="Aves" family="Fringillidae" genus="Fringilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="340" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="thoracica">
<emphasis box="[356,572,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="340">Fringilla thoracica</emphasis>
Nordmann, 1835
</taxonomicName>
(currently 
<taxonomicName box="[893,1110,836,861]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Poospiza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="340" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="thoracica">
<emphasis box="[893,1110,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="340">Poospiza thoracica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="340" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,799,1256]" pageId="11" pageNumber="340">
Included species. Monospecific; includes only 
<taxonomicName box="[745,1034,871,896]" class="Aves" family="Parulidae" genus="Castanozoster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="340" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="thoracicus">
<emphasis box="[745,1034,871,896]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="340">Castanozoster thoracicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, currently recognized as 
<taxonomicName class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Poospiza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="340" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="thoracica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="340">Poospiza thoracica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Because the name 
<emphasis box="[496,642,908,932]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="340">Castanzoster</emphasis>
is masculine in gender and 
<taxonomicName box="[976,1079,909,932]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Poospiza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="340" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[976,1079,909,932]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="340">Poospiza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is feminine, the ending of the adjectival specific epithet changes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1341,980,1005]" pageId="11" pageNumber="340" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,799,1256]" box="[199,1341,980,1005]" pageId="11" pageNumber="340">
Diagnosis. This genus is diagnosed by the specific characters of 
<taxonomicName authority="Nordmann, 1835" authorityName="Nordmann" authorityYear="1835" box="[921,1336,980,1005]" class="Aves" family="Fringillidae" genus="Fringilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="340" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="thoracica">
<emphasis box="[921,1137,980,1005]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="340">Fringilla thoracica</emphasis>
Nordmann, 1835
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="340" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,799,1256]" pageId="11" pageNumber="340">Etymology. The name is formed from the Greek καστανό (“chestnut,” both the nut and the color) and Greek ζωστήρ (“belt”), alluding to the bold chestnut band across the bird’s breast and down its flanks. Its gender is masculine.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,799,1256]" pageId="11" pageNumber="340">
Comments. 
<taxonomicName box="[337,556,1124,1149]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Poospiza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="340" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="thoracica">
<emphasis box="[337,556,1124,1149]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="340">Poospiza thoracica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to a clade of 14 other species representing six currently recognized genera in traditional classifications. Burns 
<emphasis box="[626,682,1159,1184]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="340">et al.</emphasis>
(2014) did not find strong support for the placement of 
<taxonomicName box="[1302,1436,1159,1184]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Poospiza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="340" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="thoracica">
<emphasis box="[1302,1436,1159,1184]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="340">P. thoracica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
within this clade. Thus, unless a broad genus including all 14 of these species is recognized, a new generic name is needed for 
<taxonomicName box="[277,411,1231,1256]" class="Aves" family="Emberizidae" genus="Poospiza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="340" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="thoracica">
<emphasis box="[277,411,1231,1256]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="340">P. thoracica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Accordingly, we provide 
<taxonomicName box="[710,870,1232,1256]" class="Aves" family="Parulidae" genus="Castanozoster" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="340" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="new genus">
<emphasis box="[710,870,1232,1256]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="340">Castanozoster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for this purpose.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
